## Data Payload Formats

### Device → MQTT (Sensor Data)
```json
{
  "device_id": "ESP32_SIM_01",
  "sequence_no": 42,
  "timestamp": 1708700000,
  "temperature": 28.5,
  "humidity": 62.3,
  "packet_rate": 15,
  "cpu_usage": 45,
  "battery_level": 78
}
```

### Gateway → Server (Batch)
```json
{
  "gateway_id": "gateway_001",
  "batch_id": "batch_1708700010",
  "batch_size": 5,
  "batch_hash": "sha256:abc123...",
  "logs": [ /* array of validated sensor payloads */ ]
}
```

### Server → ML Engine (Predict Request)
```json
{
  "temperature": 28.5,
  "humidity": 62.3,
  "packet_rate": 15,
  "cpu_usage": 45,
  "battery_level": 78,
  "device_id": "ESP32_SIM_01"
}
```

### ML Engine → Response
```json
{
  "anomaly_score": 0.85,
  "is_anomaly": true,
  "threats": {
    "sensor": { "anomaly": true, "score": -0.3 },
    "power": { "type": "crypto_mining", "anomaly": true },
    "behavior": { "anomaly": false }
  },
  "threat_level": "HIGH"
}
```
